xpanding Roman trade routes. In this respect, Romans treated Egyptian art surprisingly similarly to Greek art. By examining the concrete mechanisms through which Egyptian objects were acquired and displayed in Rome, this book offers a new understanding of this impressive material at the crossroads of Hellenistic, Roman, and Egyptian culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 0aArtxCollectors and collectingzItalyzRomexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aArt, EgyptianzItalyzRomexHistoryyTo 1500. 4aHandel. 4aPompeji. 4aRom / Antike. 4aWandmalerei. 4aÄgypten / Altertum. 4aÄgypten / Artefakt. 7aART / History / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aEgyptian objects.  aPompeii.  aRoman trade.  awall painting.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021 Englishz978311075405608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021z97831107538130 cEPUBz97831107009300 cprintz978311070040440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311070089340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110700893423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110700893.jpg  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Ebook Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075072-0  DG Ebook Package English 2021b2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  a978-3-11-075381-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075405-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA